article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 73, Tennessee St. 65
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- The University of Tennessee, Martin overcame a dismal start to beat Tennessee State 73-65 on Saturday. Tennessee State (5-9) took an early lead, bringing the score to 17-1 less than eight minutes into the game. Martin (4-13) spent the rest of the half playing catch up but only managed to come within 12 points of the Tigers by the end of the first half, shooting 24 percent to Tennessee State's 34.6 percent. It was 29-17 at the intermission. The Tigers continued to lead for most of the second half, but Martin's shooting improved and it finally caught the lead 44-43 with 8:26 to go. A free throw by Andrae Belton tied the game a few seconds later, but he missed the second shot and two good free throws by Will Lewis with 8:18 to go put Martin on top again -- a lead they wouldn't lose. McKale Jones led Martin with 15 points and Gerald Robinson scored another 13. McClenon Tolliver and Will Lewis scored 12 each and Zerek Knight scored 11. For Tennessee State, LaDarious Weaver scored 19 followed by Reiley Ervin with 17 and Belton with 12.
